Dialogue: 10,0:01:35.78,0:01:37.70,Top,,0,0,0,,Nice! I'm done!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:37.70,0:01:38.94,Top,,0,0,0,,Ready for half-term holiday? {lit is "midterm holiday" but book only has this in the next chapter: The weeks went quickly by. Half-term came and went. The twins’ mother came to see them at half-term and took them out in the car for the day. She was glad to see them looking so well and happy. - dunno if they mean the same thing or not; also no idea what they refer to in general, like it doesn't seem to be the same as spring/autumn holidays, in fact it seems only be two days long so I fail to see how it's different from an ordinary weekend at all lol}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:38.94,0:01:40.25,Top,,0,0,0,,Quiet, please!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:40.25,0:01:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You girls are so restless! {/can't calm down at all}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:42.97,0:01:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems the half-term holiday \Nis the only thing on your minds.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:45.72,0:01:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll have a test after the break to see how well you grasped today's material.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:51.75,0:01:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Not again! {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:53.22,0:01:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, is there anyone here whose parents
Dialogue: 10,0:01:56.15,0:01:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,won’t be visiting her over the next \Ntwo days of the holidays?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:59.75,0:02:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:00.25,0:02:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:01.67,0:02:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it. Those of you in that category \Nwill come with me to a play tomorrow afternoon.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:07.16,0:02:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:08.65,0:02:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That is all I have to say. \NLet's all have a fun half-term holiday.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:24.46,0:02:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, but it is true!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:26.15,0:02:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We have five bathrooms at home—\Nall in different colours!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:29.52,0:02:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Pink, blue, green, cream,
Dialogue: 10,0:02:33.44,0:02:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and even violet!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:36.64,0:02:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? It sounds like a fairyland!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:40.11,0:02:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We also have three cars.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:43.06,0:02:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I ever tell you about that?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:46.70,0:02:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You did, Sheila. We've heard that more times than we can count.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:49.80,0:02:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And eight servants, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:52.67,0:02:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:57.14,0:03:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet your mother will turn up \Nto collect you in a Rolls-Royce tomorrow.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:00.70,0:03:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the Rolls.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:04.18,0:03:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But my mother won't be coming here herself. {/to the school}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:07.32,0:03:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,She's staying at the best hotel in town!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:10.19,0:03:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll stay there too!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:14.08,0:03:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, come to think of it, we’ve never actually seen your mother in person, Sheila.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:17.93,0:03:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,She's too busy! Even tomorrow she's got another meeting lined up with the town's top brass.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:22.32,0:03:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, everyone, if you've ever fancied a ride in a Rolls, I can take you for a quick spin.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:29.76,0:03:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We bought a new horse the other day!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:32.01,0:03:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a terribly costly thoroughbred, \Ndescended from a Derby winner!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:42.16,0:03:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,"We have five bathrooms..." Humph!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:45.41,0:03:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if she thinks baths are only for games, \Nsince she doesn't even wash the back of her neck. {lit: despite not even washing the back of her neck - here and in the book it seems to be used literally, implying she is sloppy and inattentive: Well, it’s partly Sheila’s own silly fault,” said Hilary. “If she wouldn’t swank as she does, and try to make out she’s someone marvellous, we wouldn’t notice so easily the stupid things she does and says. I mean to say—if people swank about five different bathrooms, one pink, one blue, one green, one yellow and one mauve, and then don’t trouble to wash their necks, you do notice it rather!”}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:49.96,0:03:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, why do you think Sheila is bragging so much about being rich?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:54.13,0:03:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It was especially bad today, Janet was about to tell her everything she thinks of her! {lit: was about to explode now}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:59.22,0:04:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,She was properly getting on my nerves too!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:01.68,0:04:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,She knows full well that Doris and Kathleen have no visitors,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:04.55,0:04:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,yet she keeps on with all that \N"My mother… Rolls-Royce…" nonsense.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:08.22,0:04:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,How insensitive can she be?!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:09.80,0:04:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:11.15,0:04:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But while I feel bad for Kathleen and the others, \NI'm really looking forward to tomorrow!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:15.59,0:04:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been so long since we last saw Mum!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:31.20,0:04:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,A car! {kita = came - can't exactly go "she's here" since she's not supposed to know whose car it is}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:33.59,0:04:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Mum's car!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:38.68,0:04:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Mum!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:39.85,0:04:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello! {ohayo?}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:40.78,0:04:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello there! You two look lively. {genki}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:43.48,0:04:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! We very much are!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:45.35,0:04:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the first to come today, Mum! {of all the parents}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:47.15,0:04:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't wait to see you two.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:48.88,0:04:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Mum, you should've heard \Nhow the art teacher praised me the other day!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:53.32,0:04:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've knitted a sweater \Nin home economics class!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:55.81,0:04:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on a minute. \NWe'll have plenty of time to talk later.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:59.90,0:05:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, I must meet Headmistress.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:02.82,0:05:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:03.60,0:05:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll take you to the headmistress's office!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:05.87,0:05:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This way!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:07.01,0:05:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry! {??}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:12.25,0:05:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if she'll give us out completely. {lit: report on everything}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:14.55,0:05:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That French assignment we submitted in the middle of the night and all...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:17.85,0:05:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And the fire-cracks incident...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:19.75,0:05:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! What are we gonna do?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:24.49,0:05:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:26.49,0:05:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,D-Did Headmistress tell you anything?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:34.17,0:05:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Only that you are wonderful students, \Nalways attentive to your friends.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:39.31,0:05:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank God...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:42.14,0:05:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, how how about I drive you two out now?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:44.44,0:05:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure you have a lot to tell me about.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:46.71,0:05:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:47.50,0:05:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow! Pat's and Isabel's Mum is so gorgeous!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:52.37,0:05:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,She's elegant and she's kind. \NI'm jealous!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:57.62,0:06:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you, Madame O'Sullivan.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:00.03,0:06:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Sheila Naylor.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:02.46,0:06:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat, Isabel, and I are always socializing together.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:06.43,0:06:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The pleasure is mine, Sheila.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:07.70,0:06:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a Rolls-Royce!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:09.34,0:06:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It must be Sheila's family car!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:22.17,0:06:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you children happen to know my Sheila?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:25.60,0:06:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, she's in the same class as us.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:28.61,0:06:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Why, that's capital!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:31.09,0:06:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you ever so much for looking after my Sheila—\Nyou truly are such lovely and splendid ladies.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:36.35,0:06:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Sheila?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:37.86,0:06:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Why won't you become \Na little more ladylike yourself?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:41.42,0:06:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What's the matter with you?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:43.42,0:06:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't I tell you to stay in town?! {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:45.74,0:06:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,B-But I just had to say hello to your teachers...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:48.68,0:06:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, for goodness's sake!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:50.21,0:06:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Just drive already!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:03.37,0:07:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems to me you’ve taken quite a liking to St. Clare’s, even though you were so against it at first. {spliting at 'even' caused a 3-liner}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:09.58,0:07:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a bad school.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:11.56,0:07:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, quite decent indeed.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:14.43,0:07:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn’t mind moving you \Nto another school now, if you’d like.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:17.38,0:07:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Mum! \NWe're just fine here.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:19.61,0:07:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as you told us, the headmistress here is a wonderful person!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:23.04,0:07:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We admire Miss Roberts too.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:24.74,0:07:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And all our seniors and friends \Nare such good girls!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:27.18,0:07:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We love it here at St. Clare's!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:41.24,0:07:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Your father is eager as well to see you, \Nto know in what ways you two have changed.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:46.93,0:07:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We miss him too. {lit: we look forward to it}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:48.23,0:07:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be the best in everything—\Neven studying by then!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:51.54,0:07:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell him I'll do my very best at the next finals! {end-of-term test}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:54.96,0:07:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I look forward to it.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:59.91,0:08:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, look...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:02.47,0:08:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheila… how much longer are you going to sulk?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:05.09,0:08:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's natural for parents \Nto come to their child's school.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:08.69,0:08:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Not for all of them. {lit: It depends on the parent - meaning "there are cool parents who are cool to come to school"}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:10.77,0:08:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Did you say something?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:13.19,0:08:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nothing!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:14.49,0:08:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be happy to go shopping with you.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:16.71,0:08:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I can shop on my own just fine!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:18.46,0:08:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I can help pick the most elegant and fine clothes \Nto make you look like a proper lady.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:22.45,0:08:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I get it, all right?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:28.31,0:08:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Um... Are you Sheila's mother?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:31.54,0:08:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:32.23,0:08:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Patricia O'Sullivan.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:34.15,0:08:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Isabel O'Sullivan. \NWe are Sheila's classmates.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:38.20,0:08:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, is that so? \NI'm delighted to see you!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:41.42,0:08:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,For some reason, Sheila hates it \Nwhen I come to her school.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:44.89,0:08:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,When I ask her to introduce me to her friends, \Nshe doesn't even listen!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:47.91,0:08:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Is my Sheila studying the ways of the school as she should?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:51.03,0:08:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Yeah...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:51.92,0:08:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Um... You know, Sheila really likes to tell us about her family. Right?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:55.80,0:08:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, all the time.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:57.17,0:08:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a relief!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:58.61,0:09:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I want my Sheila to learn \Neverything good she can from St. Clare's. {says "good parts of st clare" not "at st clare" so it's closer to "learn to be like st. clare = be a proper lady"}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:02.49,0:09:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Please get along well, won't you?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:04.64,0:09:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:09.62,0:09:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Who was that?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:11.18,0:09:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheila's mother.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:12.92,0:09:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,She looks like a very amicable and kind mother.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:15.79,0:09:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,If Sheila were more like that, \Nshe'd be a lot easier to get along with.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:18.74,0:09:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:33.84,0:09:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:34.87,0:09:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:36.31,0:09:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do our best!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:48.42,0:09:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The suite where my mother and I stayed had five rooms!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:52.56,0:09:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We stayed at the most \Nexpensive suite of that hotel...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:54.86,0:09:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Give it a rest, Sheila!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:56.38,0:09:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm worried you forgot \Nyour holiday is already over! {lit: if you prolong the feeling of a holiday forever, it's a trouble - can't really think of a good english phrasing here...}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:59.32,0:10:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodness, but why oughtn't I, \Nif I'm just talking about it? {lit: oh, but if it's just talking, isn't that a good thing; in the book it was "One afternoon, just before tea, the first form were enjoying themselves in their common room. Pat put on the gramophone, and played the same record four times running. Janet looked up.\N\N“For goodness’ sake! Are you trying to learn that record by heart, Pat? Take it off and break it! If I have to hear it again I’ll scream!”\N\N“You didn’t ought to talk like that,” began Sheila, in a mincing voice—and Janet flung down her book in a rage.\N\N“Hark at Sheila! ‘Didn’t ought to!’ Good heavens, Sheila, where were you brought up? Haven’t you learnt by now that decent people don’t say ‘Didn’t ought to!’ My goodness, you talk about your servants, and your Rolls Royce cars, your horse and your lake and goodness knows what—and then you talk like the daughter of the dustman!”" - there, at least "Didn’t ought to" is bad tone I guess? but here this "yoroshiinjanai koto" is not some weird or wrong wording as far as I can tell, so I should really like to know what they were going for here - if it wasn't for a book, I'd have no idea why this phrase infuriated janet}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:04.55,0:10:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,"But why oughtn't I?"
Dialogue: 10,0:10:06.84,0:10:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did you say \Nyou were brought up again?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:09.54,0:10:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Haven’t you learnt by now that true \Ndecent people don’t say "why oughtn't I?"
Dialogue: 10,0:10:13.48,0:10:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been meaning to say this for a while...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:15.27,0:10:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm all out of patience for your haughty bragging!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:18.32,0:10:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You always talk about your life of opulence—\Nand then you talk like the daughter of the dustman! {lit: You seem to live quite comfortably, but your language is terrible.}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:23.02,0:10:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I can see right through you! {lit: to reveal one's (poor) upbringing (through poor manners, etc.); to betray one's origin; to give oneself away}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:29.43,0:10:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I-If only my people knew that St. Clare's \Nhas girls like you with no notion of manners... {book: “I’m sure that if my people knew that I had to put up with girls like you, Janet, they would never have sent me to St. Clare’s,” she began. “You’ve no manners at all, you . . .”}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:35.15,0:10:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Manners? Oh, what is it I'm hearing?\NWhat about your own manners?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:39.51,0:10:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You can begin to talk about other people’s when you know how to wash your neck
Dialogue: 10,0:10:43.34,0:10:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and brush your hair, and how to eat decently! {from book, implying she doesn't know how to do any of that}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:02.63,0:11:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet, don't you think \Nyou went too far this time? {/said too much}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:07.27,0:11:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Sheila's fault...
Dialogue: 10,0:11:09.40,0:11:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you people were just as fed up \Nwith her bravado as I am! {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:16.73,0:11:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just how Janet is.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:18.94,0:11:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,She finally lost her temper. {exploded}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:21.08,0:11:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's understandable. \NSheila's attitude can be ridiculous indeed.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:25.22,0:11:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I really don't understand Sheila. \NWhy does she need to conduct herself that way?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:29.47,0:11:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Her mother hasn’t a trace \Nof pretence about her.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:32.59,0:11:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But Sheila is the complete opposite...
Dialogue: 10,0:11:34.41,0:11:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Something must be wrong with Sheila. \NI'm quite tired of her nonsense. {line from the last NEP}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:00.32,0:12:04.12,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sheila isn't here, even though it's the evening preparation time... {book: evening preparation in the form room - whatever that is, "preparation for a lesson time" in japanese}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:04.66,0:12:08.38,Thought,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, I haven't seen her \Nduring tea time either.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:12.90,0:12:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheila...
Dialogue: 10,0:12:14.67,0:12:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't your name Pat?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:17.29,0:12:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the evening preparation time \Nfor the first formers.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:20.17,0:12:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Did something happen to Sheila?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:22.04,0:12:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. You see...
Dialogue: 10,0:12:25.38,0:12:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. It's a good thing you told me. \NI know Sheila very well.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:31.05,0:12:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:32.04,0:12:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We come from the same village—\Nher mother is the daughter of our gardener.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:38.48,0:12:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The Naylors were once terribly poor.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:41.93,0:12:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But in the end her father opened a shop, made a great success of it, and was soon comfortably off.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:48.05,0:12:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I met Sheila's mother the other day.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:50.30,0:12:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,She said she wanted Sheila to learn \Neverything good she can from St. Clare's.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:53.99,0:12:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:55.71,0:12:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,She must really want her only daughter to grow up into a graceful lady.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:59.41,0:13:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But you know, there are always those who envy the successful.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:02.31,0:13:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,They called the Naylors the upstart bumpkins.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:04.97,0:13:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:06.47,0:13:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Being poor must be awfully embarrassing to Sheila, \Nso that's what she feared the most. {being called an upstart bumpkin}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:12.02,0:13:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What she wanted the least was \Nher St. Clare's friends seeing her as an upstart. {meaning someone who comes from a poor family}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:15.76,0:13:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's why she's so reluctant\Nto introduce us to her mother?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:20.65,0:13:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,She put on this absurd, high-handed front, \Nlike a wall to keep her secrets safe.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:26.00,0:13:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But her manners and language \Nstem from the time when she was little. {lit: she was taught ...}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:30.16,0:13:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So Janet broke through that wall, \Nhitting where it hurts the most?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:35.45,0:13:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish Sheila just stayed the same as before... {instead of arguing with janet}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:38.13,0:13:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,She lacks confidence in herself, \Nso please spare a thought for her. {lit: feel sorry for her}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:42.72,0:13:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, of course!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:50.78,0:13:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheila! I was looking for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:53.73,0:13:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you unwell?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:55.47,0:13:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nothing.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:56.94,0:14:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go, then! \NIsn't it cold here?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:00.31,0:14:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:01.97,0:14:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't face you all ever again.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:04.51,0:14:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:06.08,0:14:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of what Janet said!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:09.23,0:14:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Fancy taking any notice that!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:11.08,0:14:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You know Janet always says things she doesn’t mean when she... {/is quick to lose her temper and ...}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:13.79,0:14:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We both know she said things she did mean!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:17.92,0:14:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I hate Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:19.21,0:14:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-You're right, she’s dreadfully quick-tempered and impatient, but she’s very kind too.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:28.42,0:14:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I met your mother \Nin town the other day.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:32.54,0:14:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You've such a lovely mother!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:34.57,0:14:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Lovely? Spare me your sarcasm.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:37.18,0:14:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But how can I not call her lovely \Nwhen she's so amicable, warm, and kind?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:43.20,0:14:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,She was very worried about you,\Nasked if you're studying the ways of St. Clare's... {lit: properly studying or not}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:48.17,0:14:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You bet I do!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:49.66,0:14:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm learning how to be a lady, all right?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:52.49,0:14:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheila, I'm sure you just got \Na wrong impression.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:56.88,0:14:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Wrong impression?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:58.63,0:15:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, here you are, Sheila.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:01.10,0:15:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Good timing. I need a favour from you. \NWould you help me out?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:04.67,0:15:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:18.18,0:15:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, it's beautiful!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:21.79,0:15:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,As expected of Charles's granddaughter.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:24.59,0:15:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Please don't talk about my granddad!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:26.58,0:15:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But why not?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:28.08,0:15:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to be reminded \Nthat I'm the grandchild of a gardener.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:32.06,0:15:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Please...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:40.57,0:15:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What a lovely scent.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:42.28,0:15:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Charles really was a great gardener.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:45.65,0:15:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Sheila, do you remember it? \NOur rose garden.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:56.99,0:15:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,This way, Sheila!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:58.53,0:16:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait! Wait for me, Winnie! {shortening of Winifred }
Dialogue: 10,0:16:04.95,0:16:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Charles took care of the roses with all his heart.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:09.04,0:16:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure the roses understood it too, \Nand so they always bloomed beautifully.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:13.46,0:16:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd think Charles was a magician.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:20.33,0:16:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord3.5}{because this pan has a motley ornament of roses and it's a bit hard to read}He was always such a serene \Nand dignified person.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:23.35,0:16:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord3.5}Is he doing well? {/in good health}{i guess he's still alive tho winnie clearly talked about him in past tense, but that's not always an indicator that he's dead in japanese}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:24.62,0:16:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord3.5}Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:25.82,0:16:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord3.5}He moved to the countryside \Nand is taking it easy.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:28.25,0:16:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord3.5}Your parents resemble Charles too. {??}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:31.02,0:16:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord3.5}Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:31.54,0:16:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re friendly and approachable, {lit: friendly, not picky}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:33.63,0:16:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and can understand others’ feelings so well \Nthat I can’t help but admire them.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:37.53,0:16:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-You can't be serious!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:39.15,0:16:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn’t appearance, wealth, \Nor family background that defines a person.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:43.20,0:16:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's your character that matters. {lit: what's important is what's inside}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:47.71,0:16:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheila, I really think you should be proud \Nof Charles and your parents.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:55.01,0:16:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If you excuse me...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:58.24,0:16:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheila...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:59.82,0:17:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Just being who you really are \Nis the best thing to do.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:22.88,0:17:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to apologise!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:24.43,0:17:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not asking you to apologise!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:26.65,0:17:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Just try to be a little more understanding towards Sheila.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:29.45,0:17:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You really did strike Sheila \Nwhere it hurts most—with all your might!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:33.70,0:17:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone had to knock her down a peg!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:35.96,0:17:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you're right, but you also \Nhave to avoid hurting her.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:39.19,0:17:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what it means to be friends!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:40.78,0:17:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Winifred, the head-girl, \Nalready tried talking to Sheila.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:45.63,0:17:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We should give her a chance too.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:48.13,0:17:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true. If Sheila has any common sense in her, \Nshe would try to refine her ridiculous attitude.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:53.59,0:17:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't it be infinitely better if we made Sheila change instead? Right, Janet?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:01.61,0:18:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:03.32,0:18:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,She's here!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:19.43,0:18:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:20.53,0:18:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:30.81,0:18:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheila, how about some candies?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:40.98,0:18:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Janet.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:47.64,0:18:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat and Isabel told me your mother seemed to them a really jolly, cordial person.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:53.48,0:18:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Right...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:54.95,0:18:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,She must be a wonderful person,\Ntruly the epitome of motherhood!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:59.42,0:19:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you ever introduce us? \NI'm sure I'd have loved her!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:03.16,0:19:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I was under the impression \Nshe must be an outstanding cook.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:06.21,0:19:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, Sheila!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:07.63,0:19:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, though she can manage \Nonly plain country fare…
Dialogue: 10,0:19:11.28,0:19:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like my grandma!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:12.89,0:19:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I wanna try her cooking \Nnext time she's here.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:15.15,0:19:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, Sheila. \NCould you please ask your mother?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:18.39,0:19:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, the food for the miserable \Nstarving young ladies... {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:26.80,0:19:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Mum's speciality is pies.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:28.80,0:19:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,She also likes making sweets.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:30.34,0:19:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll write her to send something over next time.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:32.56,0:19:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:33.54,0:19:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I’m certain I’ll be a marvellous cook too \Nwhen I have kids! {/when I become a parent}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:36.53,0:19:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I wouldn't have any doubts about you, Joan! \NIf you become a mum, at least your kids will eat well. {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:41.55,0:19:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:58.23,0:20:00.47,Thought,,0,0,0,,They're all so loveable people.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:00.47,0:20:03.00,Thought,,0,0,0,,In comparison, I've been so...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:03.47,0:20:06.44,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's your character that matters. {human contents}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:06.94,0:20:10.21,Thought,,0,0,0,,But what can I do to be more like them?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:14.71,0:20:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Such a nice scent!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:16.30,0:20:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder who put those here.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:18.17,0:20:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,They're wonderful!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:19.60,0:20:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Flowers are known to soothe the heart.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:22.19,0:20:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then, let's all study in high spirits.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:34.62,0:20:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, here too!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:38.55,0:20:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheila, was it you?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:40.02,0:20:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh? Yes...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:41.61,0:20:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, that must've cost you!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:43.61,0:20:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,U-Um...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:46.35,0:20:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The true worth of these roses \Nisn't in the price.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:49.15,0:20:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Only when tended with love \Ndo roses repay it by blooming beautifully.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:55.82,0:21:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted to show you \Nhow grateful I am to all of you.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:00.41,0:21:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Sheila.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:01.89,0:21:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They are wonderful roses. \NYou have great taste!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:04.11,0:21:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, they're a fancy addition to our school!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:07.33,0:21:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so? \NBut that was to be expected.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:10.00,0:21:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, I'm the granddaughter \Nof Charles, the supreme gardener!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:22.28,0:21:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheila has really begun to change.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:24.25,0:21:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a hint of her usual swagger now!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:26.52,0:21:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps too quiet now—\NI sometimes forget she’s there! {???? lit: too quiet, enough to say not enough}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:28.92,0:21:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true. She could definitely do \Nwith a bit more of self-assertion.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:32.53,0:21:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's still a huge improvement.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:34.59,0:21:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope she becomes \Neven nicer a person from now on!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:43.34,0:21:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad we decided to give Sheila a chance.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:46.59,0:21:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I guess that means \Nwe made another great friend today.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:50.71,0:21:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:52.04,0:21:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You two are talking about giving someone a chance now, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:55.18,0:21:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,This reminds me of the time we once gave a chance \Nto a certain pair of stuck-up twins before.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:59.77,0:22:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,My word, you were quite unbearable back then!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:02.32,0:22:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, at least they're \Na lot more agreeable these days.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:04.82,0:22:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:07.42,0:22:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't hurt me! {?????}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:07.79,0:22:08.88,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Get back, you! {mate?}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:08.88,0:22:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Like hell we'll give any chance to you! {???? probably means "we won't forget you for saying this"?}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:11.11,0:22:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right! You don't deserve that!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:13.10,0:22:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't need it!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:35.85,0:23:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,When we went out to town with Kathleen,
Dialogue: 10,0:23:38.48,0:23:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,we picked up an injured puppy.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:40.19,0:23:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We wanted to take him to the vet, \Nbut there's no vet practice around here.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:44.48,0:23:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So Kathleen proposed taking it to school.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:46.96,0:23:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though pets are a big no-no at our school!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:49.26,0:23:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But Katherine just loves animals too much.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:51.20,0:23:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Will she be able to take good care of it?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:52.97,0:23:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,More importantly, \Nif someone finds out about it...
Dialogue: 10,0:23:55.38,0:23:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,she'll be expelled!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:56.77,0:23:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time on Twins at St. Clare's:
Dialogue: 10,0:23:58.27,0:23:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,"Breaking the School Rules Together!" {みんなで校則やぶっちゃえ!}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.22,0:24:03.63,Note,,0,0,0,,Episode 10 \NBreaking the School Rules Together! {みんなで校則やぶっちゃえ!}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:59.97,0:24:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it!
